{"title":"create the ground truth data","markdown":{"headingText":"create the ground truth data","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"```{r data generation scatterplotbesd, echo = FALSE, results = \"hide\"}\nlibrary(tidyverse)\nlibrary(brand.yml) \nlibrary(exams)\nlibrary(kableExtra)\n\nN <- sample(50:500, 1)\nrho <- runif(1, -1, 1)\n\ndata_gt <-\n  tibble(\n    `Sozioökonomischer Status (SES)` = rnorm(N),\n    `Matheleistung (ML)` = rho *\n      `Sozioökonomischer Status (SES)` +\n      sqrt(1 - rho^2) * rnorm(N)\n  )\n\n# correlation in ground truth\nr_gt <- cor(\n  data_gt$`Sozioökonomischer Status (SES)`,\n  data_gt$`Matheleistung (ML)`\n)\n\n# BESD ground truth\nbesd_gt <- tibble(\n  Gruppe = c(\"unterUV\", \"überUV\"),\n  unterAV = c(0.5 + r_gt / 2, 0.5 - r_gt / 2),\n  überAV = c(0.5 - r_gt / 2, 0.5 + r_gt / 2)\n)\n\n# create data frame for cloze\ndata_cloze <-\n  tibble(\n    `unterdurchschn. SES` = rev(round(besd_gt$unterAV, 2)),\n    `überdurchschn. SES` = rev(round(besd_gt$überAV, 2)),\n    row_names = rev(c(\"unterdurchschn. ML\", \"überdurchschn. ML\"))\n  ) %>%\n  column_to_rownames(var = \"row_names\")\n\n````\n\n\nQuestion\n========\n### Übung {{< iconify fa7-solid:person-digging >}} {.unnumbered .h3short}\n\nIm folgenden ist die einfache lineare Regression von *N* = `r N` Datenpunkten der Variable `r names(data_gt)[1]` auf die Variable `r names(data_gt)[2]` dargestellt. \n\n```{r plot ground truth BESD}\n#| echo: false\n#| message: false\nggplot(data_gt, aes(`Sozioökonomischer Status (SES)`, `Matheleistung (ML)`)) +\n  geom_point() +\n  stat_smooth(method = \"lm\", se = F) +\n  theme(\n    axis.text.x = element_blank(),\n    axis.text.y = element_blank(),\n    axis.ticks = element_blank()\n  ) +\n  theme_brand_ggplot2()\n```\n\n\nGeben Sie in folgender Tabelle die vier Felder des Binomial Effect Size Display als Werte jeweils zwischen 0 und 1 an.\n`r add_cloze(data_cloze, tolerance = .2)`\n\n\nSolution\n========\n### Lösung:\nDie auf zwei Nachkommastellen gerundeten wahren Zahlen sind:\n```{r}\n#| label: Scatterplot-BESD-zuordnen\n#| echo: false\ndata_cloze |>\n  kable(digits = 2) |>\n  kable_styling(full_width = FALSE, position = \"left\")\n```\n\n> ALs »korrekt« wird alles gekennezichent, was ±20% genau ist.\n\nMeta-information\n================\nexname: Scatterplot-BESD-zuordnen\nextype: cloze\nexclozetype: `r format_metainfo(\"type\")`\nexsolution: `r format_metainfo(\"solution\")`\nextol: `r format_metainfo(\"tolerance\")`","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"live-html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"live-html","base-format":"html","extension-name":"live"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":"auto","echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"knitr"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true,"shortcodes":[],"brand":{"light":{"data":{"color":{"palette":{},"background":"#f2f2f2","primary":"#267326","secondary":"#d77d00","tertiary":"#0078A5"},"typography":{"fonts":[{"family":"Sou